### CLI Wrestling

Paperspace CLI installed but the command syntax is different for every service:
- `gradient models upload` — needs `--name` and `--modelType`, not `--id`
- `gradient datasets files put` — needs `--id` with version
- Neither matches the documentation exactly

Got the adapter uploaded eventually. Created an API key. Named it `mistral-notebook-cli`. The key is stored in the notebook config now so future commands should work.

### The Story Training (Prepped, Not Run)

The CADMIES narrative — Chapter I, the characters, the lore, the manifesto, the wisdom — is ready to be converted to training pairs. 18 pairs drafted covering origin story, characters, Hieros Bond, Buttercup, Number 5, the Gremlin, the soundtrack, the naming conventions, the philosophical manifesto. Will train tomorrow or next session.

## Decisions Made

- Permanent storage goes in Data (training material) and Models (trained adapters)
- Notebooks stay lean — just working files
- Adapters are just two files: weights + config. Everything else is reproducible.
- Delete training artifacts from notebook after uploading to Models
- The `cp` command works between mounted services because they're just folders
- One adapter per Models entry, not one big folder
- Story training is the next and possibly final training run

